nify\" data-icon=\"mdi:shower\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 2 Baths</span>\n196:             <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:square-foot\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 1,050 sqft</span>\n197:           </div>\n198:         </div>\n199:       </div>\n200:     </a>\n201: \n202:     <a href=\"A-07-detail.html\" style=\"text-decoration:none;color:inherit\">\n203:       <div class=\"prop-card\">\n204:         <div style=\"position:relative\">\n205:           <div class=\"prop-img\" style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(74,144,217,0.3),rgba(124,58,237,0.5))\"></div>\n206:           <button class=\"fav-btn\" style=\"position:absolute;top:12px;right:12px\"><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:heart-outline\" style=\"width:18px\"></span></button>\n207:           <span class=\"badge badge-warning\" style=\"position:absolute;top:12px;left:12px\">Featured</span>\n208:         </div>\n209:         <div class=\"prop-body\">\n210:           <div class=\"prop-price\">$2,350<small style=\"font-size:14px;font-weight:400;color:#94A3B8\">/mo</small></div>\n211:           <div class=\"prop-addr\">742 Oak Ave, Austin, TX 78702</div>\n212:           <div class=\"prop-meta\">\n213:             <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:bed\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 3 Beds</span>\n214:             <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:shower\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 2 Baths</span>\n215:             <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:square-foot\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 1,420 sqft</span>\n216:           </div>\n217:         </div>\n218:       </div>\n219:     </a>\n220: \n221:     <a href=\"A-07-detail.html\" style=\"text-decoration:none;color:inherit\">\n222:       <div class=\"prop-card\">\n223:         <div style=\"position:relative\">\n224:           <div class=\"prop-img\" style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(124,58,237,0.4),rgba(74,144,217,0.3))\"></div>\n225:           <button class=\"fav-btn\" style=\"position:absolute;top:12px;right:12px\"><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:heart-outline\" style=\"width:18px\"></span></button>\n226:         </div>\n227:         <div class=\"prop-body\">\n228:           <div class=\"prop-price\">$1,350<small style=\"font-size:14px;font-weight:400;color:#94A3B8\">/mo</small></div>\n229:           <div class=\"prop-addr\">589 Pine St, Austin, TX 78703</div>\n230:           <div class=\"prop-meta\">\n231:             <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:bed\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 1 Bed</span>\n232:             <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:shower\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 1 Bath</span>\n233:             <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:square-foot\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 720 sqft</span>\n234:           </div>\n235:         </div>\n236:       </div>\n237:     </a>\n238: \n239:     <a href=\"A-07-detail.html\" style=\"text-decoration:none;color:inherit\">\n240:       <div class=\"prop-card\">\n241:         <div style=\"position:relative\">\n242:           <div class=\"prop-img\" style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(74,144,217,0.35),rgba(124,58,237,0.35))\"></div>\n243:           <button class=\"fav-btn active\" style=\"position:absolute;top:12px;right:12px\"><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:heart\" style=\"width:18px\"></span></button>\n244:           <span class=\"badge badge-new\" style=\"position:absolute;top:12px;left:12px\">New</span>\n245:         </div>\n246:         <div class=\"prop-body\">\n247:           <div class=\"prop-price\">$2,850<small style=\"font-size:14px;font-weight:400;color:#94A3B8\">/mo</small></div>\n248:           <div class=\"prop-addr\">198 Cedar Ln, Austin, TX 78704</div>\n249:           <div class=\"prop-meta\">\n250:             <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:bed\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 3 Beds</span>\n251:             <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:shower\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 3 Baths</span>\n252:             <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:square-foot\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 1,850 sqft</span>\n253:           </div>\n254:         </div>\n255:       </div>\n256:     </a>\n257: \n258:     <div class=\"prop-card\">\n259:       <div style=\"position:relative\">\n260:         <div class=\"prop-img\" style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(74,144,217,0.5),rgba(124,58,237,0.2))\"></div>\n261:         <button class=\"fav-btn\" style=\"position:absolute;top:12px;right:12px\"><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:heart-outline\" style=\"width:18px\"></span></button>\n262:       </div>\n263:       <div class=\"prop-body\">\n264:         <div class=\"prop-price\">$975<small style=\"font-size:14px;font-weight:400;color:#94A3B8\">/mo</small></div>\n265:         <div class=\"prop-addr\">456 Willow Way, Austin, TX 78705</div>\n266:         <div class=\"prop-meta\">\n267:           <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:bed\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> Studio</span>\n268:           <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:shower\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 1 Bath</span>\n269:           <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:square-foot\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 480 sqft</span>\n270:         </div>\n271:       </div>\n272:     </div>\n273: \n274:     <div class=\"prop-card\">\n275:       <div style=\"position:relative\">\n276:         <div class=\"prop-img\" style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(74,144,217,0.25),rgba(124,58,237,0.45))\"></div>\n277:         <button class=\"fav-btn\" style=\"position:absolute;top:12px;right:12px\"><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:heart-outline\" style=\"width:18px\"></span></button>\n278:         <span class=\"badge badge-warning\" style=\"position:absolute;top:12px;left:12px\">Featured</span>\n279:       </div>\n280:       <div class=\"prop-body\">\n281:         <div class=\"prop-price\">$3,200<small style=\"font-size:14px;font-weight:400;color:#94A3B8\">/mo</small></div>\n282:         <div class=\"prop-addr\">892 Birch Dr, Austin, TX 78702</div>\n283:         <div class=\"prop-meta\">\n284:           <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:bed\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 4 Beds</span>\n285:           <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:shower\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 3 Baths</span>\n286:           <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:square-foot\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 2,300 sqft</span>\n287:         </div>\n288:       </div>\n289:     </div>\n290: \n291:     <div class=\"prop-card\">\n292:       <div style=\"position:relative\">\n293:         <div class=\"prop-img\" style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(124,58,237,0.3),rgba(74,144,217,0.4))\"></div>\n294:         <button class=\"fav-btn\" style=\"position:absolute;top:12px;right:12px\"><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:heart-outline\" style=\"width:18px\"></span></button>\n295:       </div>\n296:       <div class=\"prop-body\">\n297:         <div class=\"prop-price\">$1,650<small style=\"font-size:14px;font-weight:400;color:#94A3B8\">/mo</small></div>\n298:         <div class=\"prop-addr\">112 Maple St, Austin, TX 78701</div>\n299:         <div class=\"prop-meta\">\n300:           <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:bed\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 2 Beds</span>\n301:           <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:shower\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 1 Bath</span>\n302:           <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:square-foot\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 980 sqft</span>\n303:         </div>\n304:       </div>\n305:     </div>\n306: \n307:     <div class=\"prop-card\">\n308:       <div style=\"position:relative\">\n309:         <div class=\"prop-img\" style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(74,144,217,0.3),rgba(124,58,237,0.3))\"></div>\n310:         <button class=\"fav-btn\" style=\"position:absolute;top:12px;right:12px\"><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:heart-outline\" style=\"width:18px\"></span></button>\n311:         <span class=\"badge badge-new\" style=\"position:absolute;top:12px;left:12px\">New</span>\n312:       </div>\n313:       <div class=\"prop-body\">\n314:         <div class=\"prop-price\">$2,100<small style=\"font-size:14px;font-weight:400;color:#94A3B8\">/mo</small></div>\n315:         <div class=\"prop-addr\">655 Spruce Ct, Austin, TX 78703</div>\n316:         <div class=\"prop-meta\">\n317:           <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:bed\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 2 Beds</span>\n318:           <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:shower\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 2 Baths</span>\n319:           <span><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:square-foot\" style=\"width:14px\"></span> 1,100 sqft</span>\n320:         </div>\n321:       </div>\n322:     </div>\n323:   </div>\n324: \n325:   <div class=\"pagination\">\n326:     <button class=\"page-btn\"><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:chevron-left\" style=\"width:18px\"></span></button>\n327:     <button class=\"page-btn active\">1</button>\n328:     <button class=\"page-btn\">2</button>\n329:     <button class=\"page-btn\">3</button>\n330:     <button class=\"page-btn\">4</button>\n331:     <button class=\"page-btn\">5</button>\n332:     <button class=\"page-btn\">...</button>\n333:     <button class=\"page-btn\">8</button>\n334:     <button class=\"page-btn\"><span class=\"iconify\" data-icon=\"mdi:chevron-right\" style=\"width:18px\"></span></button>\n335:   </div>\n336: </section>\n337: </div>\n338: </body>\n339: </html>\n\n(End of file - total 339 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <title>NestFind — Search Properties</title>\n  <link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com\">\n  <link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n  <script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@iconify/iconify@2.2.1/dist/iconify.min.js\"></script>\n  <style>\n*{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}\nbody{font-family:'Inter',system-ui,sans-serif;background:#0B0F1A;color:#F1F5F9;line-height:1.6}\n.root{max-width:1440px;margin:0 auto}\n.navbar{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;padding:16px 48px;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08)}\n.nav-logo{font-size:24px;font-weight:700;background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4A90D9,#7C3AED);-webkit-background-clip:text;-webkit-text-fill-color:transparent}\n.nav-links{display:flex;gap:32px;align-items:center}\n.nav-links a{color:#94A3B8;text-decoration:none;font-size:14px;font-weight:500;transition:color 0.2s}\n.nav-links a:hover{color:#F1F5F9}\n.btn{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;gap:8px;font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;border:none;transition:all 0.2s;font-family:inherit;text-decoration:none}\n.btn-primary{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4A90D9,#7C3AED);color:#fff;height:48px;padding:0 24px;border-radius:12px;font-size:14px}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude-project/nestfind/design/html/frontend/A-06-search.html","time":{"start":1779192372839,"end":1779192373131}},"id":"prt_e402117d7001XlqyfePiU3lLn7","sessionID":"ses_1bfdf015dffez1iatzFjbXquMi","messageID":"msg_e4021024e001jAeAIuo25tlW5a"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779192374943,"sessionID":"ses_1bfdf015dffez1iatzFjbXquMi","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_Kg82o4WVdCIqOEYMWevB6192","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/renter/search.tsx"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/renter/search.tsx</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: export default function SearchPage() {\n2:   return (\n3:     <div className=\"py-8 w-full\">\n4:       <h1 className=\"text-3xl font-bold\">Search Properties</h1>\n5:       <p className=\"mt-2 text-muted-foreground\">Find your perfect rental home.</p>\n6:     </div>\n7:   );\n8: }\n\n(End of file - total 8 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"export default function SearchPage() {\n  return (\n    <div className=\"py-8 w-full\">\n      <h1 className=\"text-3xl font-bold\">Search Properties</h1>\n      <p className=\"mt-2 text-muted-foreground\">Find your perfect rental home.</p>\n    </div>\n  );\n}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"frontend/app/pages/renter/search.tsx","time":{"start":1779192374653,"end":1779192374942}},"id":"prt_e40211fb1001AcfriZdfAqH6k5","sessionID":"ses_1bfdf015dffez1iatzFjbXquMi","messageID":"msg_e4021024e001jAeAIuo25tlW5a"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779192376687,"sessionID":"ses_1bfdf015dffez1iatzFjbXquMi","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02_xw6VM4slxhPSswnK9BtA4788","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/component-patterns.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/component-patterns.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Component Patterns\n2: \n3: Modern component architecture using Shadcn/UI, Tailwind CSS, and TypeScript.\n4: \n5: ---\n6: \n7: ## Function Component Pattern (PREFERRED)\n8: \n9: ### Why Function Components\n10: \n11: All components use function components with TypeScript for:\n12: \n13: - Explicit type safety for props\n14: - Consistent component signatures\n15: - Clear prop interface documentation\n16: - Better IDE autocomplete\n17: \n18: ### Basic Pattern\n19: \n20: ```typescript\n21: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n22: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n23: \n24: interface MyComponentProps {\n25:   /** User ID to display */\n26:   userId: number;\n27:   /** Optional callback when action occurs */\n28:   onAction?: () => void;\n29: }\n30: \n31: export default function MyComponent({ userId, onAction }: MyComponentProps) {\n32:   return (\n33:     <div className=\"p-4\">\n34:       User: {userId}\n35:       <Button onClick={onAction}>Action</Button>\n36:     </div>\n37:   );\n38: }\n39: ```\n40: \n41: **Key Points:**\n42: \n43: - Props interface defined separately with JSDoc comments\n44: - Destructure props in parameters\n45: - Default export at bottom\n46: - Use Tailwind classes for styling\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## Shadcn/UI Component Usage\n51: \n52: ### Available Components\n53: \n54: Shadcn/UI components are in `~/components/ui/`:\n55: \n56: ```typescript\n57: // Buttons\n58: import { Button, buttonVariants } from '~/components/ui/button';\n59: \n60: // Forms\n61: import { Input } from '~/components/ui/input';\n62: import { Label } from '~/components/ui/label';\n63: import {\n64:   Form,\n65:   FormControl,\n66:   FormField,\n67:   FormItem,\n68:   FormLabel,\n69:   FormMessage,\n70: } from '~/components/ui/form';\n71: \n72: // Cards\n73: import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from '~/components/ui/card';\n74: ```\n75: \n76: ### Button Component\n77: \n78: ```typescript\n79: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n80: \n81: // Variants\n82: <Button variant=\"default\">Primary</Button>\n83: <Button variant=\"secondary\">Secondary</Button>\n84: <Button variant=\"destructive\">Delete</Button>\n85: <Button variant=\"outline\">Outlined</Button>\n86: <Button variant=\"ghost\">Ghost</Button>\n87: <Button variant=\"link\">Link</Button>\n88: \n89: // Sizes\n90: <Button size=\"sm\">Small</Button>\n91: <Button size=\"default\">Default</Button>\n92: <Button size=\"lg\">Large</Button>\n93: <Button size=\"icon\"><Icon /></Button>\n94: \n95: // States\n96: <Button disabled>Disabled</Button>\n97: <Button className=\"w-full\">Full Width</Button>\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ### Card Component\n101: \n102: ```typescript\n103: import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from '~/components/ui/card';\n104: \n105: <Card className=\"w-full max-w-md\">\n106:   <CardHeader>\n107:     <CardTitle>Card Title</CardTitle>\n108:   </CardHeader>\n109:   <CardContent className=\"space-y-4\">\n110:     <p>Card content goes here</p>\n111:   </CardContent>\n112: </Card>\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ### Form Components (MANDATORY PATTERN — all forms must use this)\n116: \n117: ```typescript\n118: import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';\n119: import { zodResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/zod';\n120: import { z } from 'zod';\n121: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n122: import { Input } from '~/components/ui/input';\n123: import {\n124:   Form,\n125:   FormControl,\n126:   FormField,\n127:   FormItem,\n128:   FormLabel,\n129:   FormMessage,\n130: } from '~/components/ui/form';\n131: \n132: const schema = z.object({\n133:   email: z.string().email(),\n134:   password: z.string().min(6),\n135: });\n136: \n137: type FormData = z.infer<typeof schema>;\n138: \n139: export default function LoginForm() {\n140:   const form = useForm<FormData>({\n141:     resolver: zodResolver(schema),\n142:     defaultValues: { email: '', password: '' },\n143:   });\n144: \n145:   return (\n146:     <Form {...form}>\n147:       <form onSubmit={form.handleSubmit(onSubmit)} className=\"space-y-4\">\n148:         <FormField\n149:           control={form.control}\n150:           name=\"email\"\n151:           render={({ field }) => (\n152:             <FormItem>\n153:               <FormLabel>Email</FormLabel>\n154:               <FormControl>\n155:                 <Input placeholder=\"Enter email\" {...field} />\n156:               </FormControl>\n157:               <FormMessage />\n158:             </FormItem>\n159:           )}\n160:         />\n161:         <Button type=\"submit\">Submit</Button>\n162:       </form>\n163:     </Form>\n164:   );\n165: }\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ## CVA (Class Variance Authority)\n171: \n172: ### What is CVA\n173: \n174: CVA is used for component variants in Shadcn/UI. It creates type-safe variant props.\n175: \n176: ### Example from Button Component\n177: \n178: ```typescript\n179: import { cva, type VariantProps } from 'class-variance-authority';\n180: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n181: \n182: const buttonVariants = cva(\n183:   // Base styles applied to all buttons\n184:   'inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md text-sm font-medium transition-all',\n185:   {\n186:     variants: {\n187:       variant: {\n188:         default: 'bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90',\n189:         destructive: 'bg-destructive text-white hover:bg-destructive/90',\n190:         outline: 'border bg-background hover:bg-accent',\n191:         secondary: 'bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground hover:bg-secondary/80',\n192:         ghost: 'hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground',\n193:         link: 'text-primary underline-offset-4 hover:underline',\n194:       },\n195:       size: {\n196:         default: 'h-9 px-4 py-2',\n197:         sm: 'h-8 px-3',\n198:         lg: 'h-10 px-6',\n199:         icon: 'size-9',\n200:       },\n201:     },\n202:     defaultVariants: {\n203:       variant: 'default',\n204:       size: 'default',\n205:     },\n206:   }\n207: );\n208: \n209: // Usage in component\n210: function Button({\n211:   className,\n212:   variant,\n213:   size,\n214:   ...props\n215: }: React.ComponentProps<'button'> & VariantProps<typeof buttonVariants>) {\n216:   return (\n217:     <button\n218:       className={cn(buttonVariants({ variant, size, className }))}\n219:       {...props}\n220:     />\n221:   );\n222: }\n223: ```\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ## When to Add a Variant vs Use className (MANDATORY)\n228: \n229: All reusable components must follow these rules:\n230: \n231: 1. **Every reusable component MUST accept a `className` prop** — this allows call-site-specific layout overrides\n232: 2. **Add a cva variant when:**\n233:    - The style combination appears at 2+ call sites\n234:    - It represents a semantic state (error, success, warning, loading, ghost, compact)\n235:    - It changes the visual identity of the component (not just layout)\n236: 3. **Use `className` when:**\n237:    - The override is context-specific and used at only 1 call site\n238:    - It's a layout concern (width, height, padding offset, positioning)\n239:    - It's a dynamic value passed from props (e.g., `className={style.text}`)\n240: \n241: ```typescript\n242: // ✅ CORRECT — Semantic state as variant\n243: <Input variant=\"error\" />\n244: \n245: // ✅ CORRECT — One-off layout as className\n246: <Input className=\"pl-10\" />\n247: \n248: // ❌ WRONG — Duplicated error classes at call sites\n249: <Input className=\"border-red-400 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-red-500/20\" />\n250: \n251: // ❌ WRONG — Creating a new component for a style difference\n252: // Instead, add a variant to the existing component\n253: ```\n254: \n255: ---\n256: \n257: ## cn() Utility for Class Merging\n258: \n259: ### What is cn()\n260: \n261: `cn()` combines `clsx` and `tailwind-merge` for conditional class merging:\n262: \n263: ```typescript\n264: // ~/lib/utils.ts\n265: import { clsx, type ClassValue } from 'clsx';\n266: import { twMerge } from 'tailwind-merge';\n267: \n268: export function cn(...inputs: ClassValue[]) {\n269:   return twMerge(clsx(inputs));\n270: }\n271: ```\n272: \n273: ### Usage Examples\n274: \n275: ```typescript\n276: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n277: \n278: // Conditional classes\n279: <div className={cn(\n280:   'p-4 bg-background',\n281:   isActive && 'bg-primary text-primary-foreground',\n282:   isDisabled && 'opacity-50 pointer-events-none'\n283: )} />\n284: \n285: // Merging with overrides\n286: <Button className={cn(\n287:   buttonVariants({ variant: 'default' }),\n288:   'w-full' // Override width\n289: )} />\n290: \n291: // Array of conditions\n292: <div className={cn([\n293:   'base-class',\n294:   condition1 && 'class-1',\n295:   condition2 && 'class-2',\n296: ])} />\n297: ```\n298: \n299: ---\n300: \n301: ## asChild Pattern (Radix UI)\n302: \n303: ### What is asChild\n304: \n305: The `asChild` prop allows composing components with custom elements:\n306: \n307: ```typescript\n308: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n309: import { Link } from 'react-router';\n310: \n311: // Button as Link\n312: <Button asChild>\n313:   <Link to=\"/dashboard\">Go to Dashboard</Link>\n314: </Button>\n315: \n316: // Button as anchor\n317: <Button asChild variant=\"link\">\n318:   <a href=\"https://example.com\">External Link</a>\n319: </Button>\n320: ```\n321: \n322: ### How it Works\n323: \n324: The Button uses Radix's `Slot` component:\n325: \n326: ```typescript\n327: import { Slot } from '@radix-ui/react-slot';\n328: \n329: function Button({ asChild = false, ...props }) {\n330:   const Comp = asChild ? Slot : 'button';\n331:   return <Comp {...props} />;\n332: }\n333: ```\n334: \n335: ### IMPORTANT: asChild + Link Anti-Pattern\n336: \n337: **NEVER use `asChild` with `Link` inside `DropdownMenuItem`:**\n338: \n339: ```typescript\n340: // ❌ CAUSES VISUAL \"BLINK\" ON FIRST RENDER\n341: <DropdownMenuItem asChild>\n342:   <Link to={`/dashboard/users/${user.id}`}>\n343:     <Eye className=\"mr-2 h-4 w-4\" />\n344:     View Details\n345:   </Link>\n346: </DropdownMenuItem>\n347: \n348: // ✅ USE onClick with navigate() INSTEAD\n349: <DropdownMenuItem onClick={() => navigate(`/dashboard/users/${user.id}`)}>\n350:   <Eye className=\"mr-2 h-4 w-4\" />\n351:   View Details\n352: </DropdownMenuItem>\n353: ```\n354: \n355: **Better: Use the ActionMenu Component**\n356: \n357: For table action menus, use the reusable `ActionMenu` component:\n358: \n359: ```typescript\n360: import { ActionMenu } from '~/components/ui/action-menu';\n361: \n362: <ActionMenu\n363:   items={[\n364:     {\n365:       label: 'View Details',\n366:       icon: <Eye className=\"mr-2 h-4 w-4\" />,\n367:       href: `/dashboard/users/${user.id}`,  // Uses navigate() internally\n368:     },\n369:     {\n370:       label: 'Delete',\n371:       icon: <Trash2 className=\"mr-2 h-4 w-4\" />,\n372:       onClick: () => handleDelete(user.id),\n373:       variant: 'destructive',\n374:     },\n375:   ]}\n376: />\n377: ```\n378: \n379: ---\n380: \n381: ## Component Structure Template\n382: \n383: ### Recommended Order\n384: \n385: ```typescript\n386: import { useState, useCallback, useMemo, useEffect } from 'react';\n387: import { Link } from 'react-router';\n388: \n389: // Redux\n390: import { useAppDispatch, useAppSelector } from '~/redux/store/hooks';\n391: \n392: // UI Components\n393: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n394: import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader } from '~/components/ui/card';\n395: \n396: // Utilities\n397: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n398: \n399: // Types\n400: import type { User } from '~/types/user';\n401: \n402: // 1. PROPS INTERFACE (with JSDoc)\n403: interface MyComponentProps {\n404:   /** The ID of the entity to display */\n405:   entityId: number;\n406:   /** Optional callback when action completes */\n407:   onComplete?: () => void;\n408:   /** Display mode */\n409:   mode?: 'view' | 'edit';\n410: }\n411: \n412: // 2. COMPONENT DEFINITION\n413: export default function MyComponent({\n414:   entityId,\n415:   onComplete,\n416:   mode = 'view',\n417: }: MyComponentProps) {\n418:   // 3. HOOKS (in this order)\n419:   // - Redux hooks\n420:   const dispatch = useAppDispatch();\n421:   const user = useAppSelector((state) => state.user.currentUser);\n422:   const loading = useAppSelector((state) => state.user.loading);\n423: \n424:   // - Local state\n425:   const [selectedItem, setSelectedItem] = useState<string | null>(null);\n426:   const [isEditing, setIsEditing] = useState(mode === 'edit');\n427: \n428:   // - Memoized values\n429:   const filteredData = useMemo(() => {\n430:     return data.filter((item) => item.active);\n431:   }, [data]);\n432: \n433:   // - Effects\n434:   useEffect(() => {\n435:     // Setup\n436:     return () => {\n437:       // Cleanup\n438:     };\n439:   }, []);\n440: \n441:   // 4. EVENT HANDLERS (with useCallback for passed handlers)\n442:   const handleItemSelect = useCallback((itemId: string) => {\n443:     setSelectedItem(itemId);\n444:   }, []);\n445: \n446:   const handleSave = useCallback(async () => {\n447:     try {\n448:       // Save logic\n449:       onComplete?.();\n450:     } catch (error) {\n451:       console.error('Failed to save:', error);\n452:     }\n453:   }, [onComplete]);\n454: \n455:   // 5. RENDER\n456:   return (\n457:     <Card className=\"w-full max-w-md\">\n458:       <CardHeader>\n459:         <h2 className=\"text-xl font-bold\">My Component</h2>\n460:       </CardHeader>\n461:       <CardContent className=\"space-y-4\">\n462:         <p className={cn('text-muted-foreground', loading && 'opacity-50')}>\n463:           {user?.email}\n464:         </p>\n465:         <Button onClick={handleSave} disabled={loading}>\n466:           {loading ? 'Loading...' : 'Save'}\n467:         </Button>\n468:       </CardContent>\n469:     </Card>\n470:   );\n471: }\n472: ```\n473: \n474: ---\n475: \n476: ## Component Separation\n477: \n478: ### When to Split Components\n479: \n480: **Split into multiple components when:**\n481: \n482: - Component exceeds 200 lines\n483: - Multiple distinct responsibilities\n484: - Reusable sections\n485: - Complex nested JSX\n486: \n487: **Example:**\n488: \n489: ```typescript\n490: // ❌ AVOID - Monolithic\n491: function MassivePage() {\n492:   // 500+ lines\n493:   // Header logic\n494:   // Form logic\n495:   // Table logic\n496:   // Modal logic\n497: }\n498: \n499: // ✅ PREFERRED - Modular\n500: function Page() {\n501:   return (\n502:     <div className=\"space-y-6\">\n503:       <PageHeader />\n504:       <SearchForm onSearch={handleSearch} />\n505:       <DataTable data={filteredData} />\n506:       <ActionModal open={isOpen} onClose={handleClose} />\n507:     </div>\n508:   );\n509: }\n510: ```\n511: \n512: ### When to Keep Together\n513: \n514: **Keep in same file when:**\n515: \n516: - Component < 100 lines\n517: - Tightly coupled logic\n518: - Not reusable elsewhere\n519: - Simple presentation component\n520: \n521: ---\n522: \n523: ## Lazy Loading Pattern\n524: \n525: ### When to Lazy Load\n526: \n527: Lazy load components that are:\n528: \n529: - Heavy (DataGrid, charts, rich text editors)\n530: - Route-level components\n531: - Modal/dialog content (not shown initially)\n532: - Below-the-fold content\n533: \n534: ### How to Lazy Load\n535: \n536: ```typescript\n537: import { lazy, Suspense } from 'react';\n538: \n539: // Lazy load heavy component\n540: const HeavyEditor = lazy(() => import('./HeavyEditor'));\n541: \n542: // Usage with Suspense\n543: function Page() {\n544:   return (\n545:     <Suspense fallback={<div>Loading...</div>}>\n546:       <HeavyEditor />\n547:     </Suspense>\n548:   );\n549: }\n550: ```\n551: \n552: ---\n553: \n554: ## Component Communication\n555: \n556: ### Props Down, Events Up\n557: \n558: ```typescript\n559: // Parent\n560: function Parent() {\n561:   const [selectedId, setSelectedId] = useState<string | null>(null);\n562: \n563:   return (\n564:     <Child\n565:       data={data} // Props down\n566:       onSelect={setSelectedId} // Events up\n567:     />\n568:   );\n569: }\n570: \n571: // Child\n572: interface ChildProps {\n573:   data: Data[];\n574:   onSelect: (id: string) => void;\n575: }\n576: \n577: export default function Child({ data, onSelect }: ChildProps) {\n578:   return (\n579:     <ul>\n580:       {data.map((item) => (\n581:         <li key={item.id} onClick={() => onSelect(item.id)}>\n582:           {item.name}\n583:         </li>\n584:       ))}\n585:     </ul>\n586:   );\n587: }\n588: ```\n589: \n590: ### Using Redux for Shared State\n591: \n592: ```typescript\n593: // When state needs to be shared across components\n594: import { useAppDispatch, useAppSelector } from '~/redux/store/hooks';\n595: import { selectItem } from '~/redux/features/itemSlice';\n596: \n597: function Child() {\n598:   const dispatch = useAppDispatch();\n599:   const selectedId = useAppSelector((state) => state.item.selectedId);\n600: \n601:   const handleSelect = (id: string) => {\n602:     dispatch(selectItem(id));\n603:   };\n604: \n605:   return <div onClick={() => handleSelect('123')}>Select</div>;\n606: }\n607: ```\n608: \n609: ---\n610: \n611: ## Summary\n612: \n613: **Modern Component Recipe:**\n614: \n615: 1. Function components with TypeScript props interface\n616: 2. Shadcn/UI components from `~/components/ui/`\n617: 3. `cn()` utility for conditional classes\n618: 4. Tailwind CSS for styling\n619: 5. `useAppSelector` and `useAppDispatch` for Redux\n620: 6. Event handlers with `useCallback` when passed to children\n621: 7. Default export at bottom\n622: \n623: ---\n624: \n625: ## MANDATORY: Async State Handling\n626: \n627: Every component that fetches data MUST handle all three states:\n628: \n629: ```typescript\n630: // MANDATORY: Loading state\n631: if (isLoading) return <LoadingSkeleton />;\n632: \n633: // MANDATORY: Error state\n634: if (error) return <ErrorState message={error.message} onRetry={refetch} />;\n635: \n636: // MANDATORY: Empty state (distinct from error)\n637: if (!data?.length) return <EmptyState title=\"No items found\" />;\n638: \n639: // Happy path\n640: return <DataList items={data} />;\n641: ```\n642: \n643: **Rules:**\n644: - Loading skeleton (not spinner) for initial data loads\n645: - Error state with retry button for API failures\n646: - Empty state for zero results (NOT the same component as error)\n647: - Error boundaries wrapping route-level components for uncaught errors\n648: \n649: ## MANDATORY: No Business Logic in Components\n650: \n651: Components must only handle rendering and event delegation:\n652: \n653: ```typescript\n654: // BAD: Business logic in component\n655: const filteredUsers = users.filter(u => u.role === 'admin' && u.isActive);\n656: const sortedUsers = filteredUsers.sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));\n657: \n658: // GOOD: Logic in selector/utility\n659: const activeAdmins = useAppSelector(selectActiveAdmins);\n660: ```\n661: \n662: **See Also:**\n663: \n664: - [styling-guide.md](styling-guide.md) - Tailwind CSS patterns\n665: - [common-patterns.md](common-patterns.md) - Form patterns\n666: - [complete-examples.md](complete-examples.md) - Full working examples\n\n(End of file - total 666 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Component Patterns\n\nModern component architecture using Shadcn/UI, Tailwind CSS, and TypeScript.\n\n---\n\n## Function Component Pattern (PREFERRED)\n\n### Why Function Components\n\nAll components use function components with TypeScript for:\n\n- Explicit type safety for props\n- Consistent component signatures\n- Clear prop interface documentation\n- Better IDE autocomplete\n\n### Basic Pattern\n\n```typescript","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/docs/component-patterns.md","time":{"start":1779192376401,"end":1779192376686}},"id":"prt_e402126c5001XFoZLgExfZiRa5","sessionID":"ses_1bfdf015dffez1iatzFjbXquMi","messageID":"msg_e4021024e001jAeAIuo25tlW5a"}}
