{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779192388068,"sessionID":"ses_1bfdf015dffez1iatzFjbXquMi","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02_9HV0SP6hiaVaGg9pupA96938","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/components/layouts/RenterLayout.tsx"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/components/layouts/RenterLayout.tsx</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: import { Outlet, Navigate, useLocation } from 'react-router';\n2: import { useAuth } from '~/hooks/useAuth';\n3: import Header from '~/components/layout/header';\n4: import { Loader2 } from 'lucide-react';\n5: import { RoleEnum } from '~/enums/role.enum';\n6: \n7: const routeAccess: Record<string, Array<string | number>> = {\n8:   '/search': [RoleEnum.RENTER, RoleEnum.ADMIN],\n9:   '/favorites': [RoleEnum.RENTER],\n10:   '/inquiries': [RoleEnum.RENTER],\n11:   '/profile': [RoleEnum.RENTER, RoleEnum.ADMIN],\n12: };\n13: \n14: export default function RenterLayout() {\n15:   const { isAuthenticated, authChecked, user } = useAuth();\n16:   const location = useLocation();\n17: \n18:   if (!authChecked) {\n19:     return (\n20:       <div className=\"flex h-screen items-center justify-center\">\n21:         <Loader2 className=\"h-8 w-8 animate-spin text-primary\" />\n22:       </div>\n23:     );\n24:   }\n25: \n26:   if (!isAuthenticated || !user) {\n27:     return <Navigate to=\"/login\" replace />;\n28:   }\n29: \n30:   const currentPath = '/' + location.pathname.split('/').filter(Boolean)[0];\n31:   const allowedRoles = routeAccess[currentPath];\n32:   if (allowedRoles && !allowedRoles.map(String).includes(String(user.role))) {\n33:     return <Navigate to=\"/unauthorized\" replace />;\n34:   }\n35: \n36:   return (\n37:     <div className=\"relative min-h-screen flex flex-col\">\n38:       <Header />\n39:       <main className=\"container mx-auto flex-1 flex px-4\">\n40:         <Outlet />\n41:       </main>\n42:     </div>\n43:   );\n44: }\n\n(End of file - total 44 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"import { Outlet, Navigate, useLocation } from 'react-router';\nimport { useAuth } from '~/hooks/useAuth';\nimport Header from '~/components/layout/header';\nimport { Loader2 } from 'lucide-react';\nimport { RoleEnum } from '~/enums/role.enum';\n\nconst routeAccess: Record<string, Array<string | number>> = {\n  '/search': [RoleEnum.RENTER, RoleEnum.ADMIN],\n  '/favorites': [RoleEnum.RENTER],\n  '/inquiries': [RoleEnum.RENTER],\n  '/profile': [RoleEnum.RENTER, RoleEnum.ADMIN],\n};\n\nexport default function RenterLayout() {\n  const { isAuthenticated, authChecked, user } = useAuth();\n  const location = useLocation();\n\n  if (!authChecked) {\n    return (\n      <div className=\"flex h-screen items-center justify-center\">","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"frontend/app/components/layouts/RenterLayout.tsx","time":{"start":1779192387777,"end":1779192388066}},"id":"prt_e40215309001ff1AbvSRxzLoYE","sessionID":"ses_1bfdf015dffez1iatzFjbXquMi","messageID":"msg_e40212f4a001cWeCSVzimIsYkT"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779192389890,"sessionID":"ses_1bfdf015dffez1iatzFjbXquMi","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_03_uRTh8iWDFI1I98X51d3S2427","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/i18n-architecture.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/i18n-architecture.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # i18n Architecture Guide\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: When a project requires multilingual support, use `react-i18next` for internationalization.\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Setup\n10: \n11: ### 1. Install Dependencies\n12: \n13: ```bash\n14: npm install react-i18next i18next i18next-http-backend i18next-browser-languagedetector\n15: ```\n16: \n17: ### 2. Create i18n Configuration\n18: \n19: ```typescript\n20: // app/i18n.ts\n21: import i18n from 'i18next';\n22: import { initReactI18next } from 'react-i18next';\n23: import LanguageDetector from 'i18next-browser-languagedetector';\n24: import Backend from 'i18next-http-backend';\n25: \n26: i18n\n27:   .use(Backend)\n28:   .use(LanguageDetector)\n29:   .use(initReactI18next)\n30:   .init({\n31:     fallbackLng: 'en',\n32:     supportedLngs: ['en', 'ko'],\n33:     defaultNS: 'translation',\n34:     interpolation: {\n35:       escapeValue: false, // React already escapes\n36:     },\n37:     backend: {\n38:       loadPath: '/locales/{{lng}}/{{ns}}.json',\n39:     },\n40:   });\n41: \n42: export default i18n;\n43: ```\n44: \n45: ### 3. Create Locale Files\n46: \n47: ```\n48: public/\n49: └── locales/\n50:     ├── en/\n51:     │   └── translation.json\n52:     └── ko/\n53:         └── translation.json\n54: ```\n55: \n56: ```json\n57: // public/locales/en/translation.json\n58: {\n59:   \"common\": {\n60:     \"save\": \"Save\",\n61:     \"cancel\": \"Cancel\",\n62:     \"delete\": \"Delete\",\n63:     \"loading\": \"Loading...\",\n64:     \"noResults\": \"No results found\",\n65:     \"error\": \"Something went wrong\"\n66:   },\n67:   \"auth\": {\n68:     \"login\": \"Login\",\n69:     \"logout\": \"Logout\",\n70:     \"email\": \"Email\",\n71:     \"password\": \"Password\"\n72:   }\n73: }\n74: ```\n75: \n76: ### 4. Initialize in Entry Point\n77: \n78: ```typescript\n79: // root.tsx\n80: import './i18n';\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ---\n84: \n85: ## Usage in Components\n86: \n87: ### Basic Translation\n88: \n89: ```typescript\n90: import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next';\n91: \n92: export const SaveButton = () => {\n93:   const { t } = useTranslation();\n94:   return <button>{t('common.save')}</button>;\n95: };\n96: ```\n97: \n98: ### With Variables\n99: \n100: ```typescript\n101: // translation.json: \"welcome\": \"Hello, {{name}}!\"\n102: <p>{t('welcome', { name: user.name })}</p>\n103: ```\n104: \n105: ### Plurals\n106: \n107: ```typescript\n108: // translation.json: \"items_one\": \"{{count}} item\", \"items_other\": \"{{count}} items\"\n109: <span>{t('items', { count: itemCount })}</span>\n110: ```\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: ## Language Switcher\n115: \n116: ```typescript\n117: import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next';\n118: \n119: export const LanguageSwitcher = () => {\n120:   const { i18n } = useTranslation();\n121: \n122:   return (\n123:     <select\n124:       value={i18n.language}\n125:       onChange={(e) => i18n.changeLanguage(e.target.value)}\n126:     >\n127:       <option value=\"en\">English</option>\n128:       <option value=\"ko\">한국어</option>\n129:     </select>\n130:   );\n131: };\n132: ```\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: ## MANDATORY Rules\n137: \n138: - **Every visible string** in UI components MUST use `t()` — no hardcoded text\n139: - **Locale files** must exist for ALL supported languages before shipping\n140: - **Keys** use dot notation organized by feature: `auth.login`, `dashboard.title`\n141: - **Fallback language** must always be set (typically `en`)\n142: - **Do NOT** use string concatenation for translated strings — use interpolation variables\n143: - **Form validation messages** should also be translated via Zod `.refine()` with `t()`\n144: \n145: ## E2E Testing with i18n\n146: \n147: When writing Playwright tests for i18n apps:\n148: - Use `[data-testid]` selectors (language-independent) — preferred\n149: - Or bilingual regex: `button:has-text(/Save|저장/i)`\n150: - NEVER use English-only text selectors when default locale is not English\n151: \n152: ---\n153: \n154: ## Related\n155: \n156: - [best-practices.md](best-practices.md) — Coding standards\n157: - [component-patterns.md](component-patterns.md) — Component structure\n158: - [typescript-standards.md](typescript-standards.md) — Type safety\n\n(End of file - total 158 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# i18n Architecture Guide\n\n## Overview\n\nWhen a project requires multilingual support, use `react-i18next` for internationalization.\n\n---\n\n## Setup\n\n### 1. Install Dependencies\n\n```bash\nnpm install react-i18next i18next i18next-http-backend i18next-browser-languagedetector\n```\n\n### 2. Create i18n Configuration\n\n```typescript\n// app/i18n.ts","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/docs/i18n-architecture.md","time":{"start":1779192389580,"end":1779192389889}},"id":"prt_e40215a0e001hDYrt41DiQax5F","sessionID":"ses_1bfdf015dffez1iatzFjbXquMi","messageID":"msg_e40212f4a001cWeCSVzimIsYkT"}}
