{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779192454776,"sessionID":"ses_1bfdf015dffez1iatzFjbXquMi","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_jE2IqTfeF6e3PU6njsN94470","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/components/layout/header.tsx"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/components/layout/header.tsx</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: import { Link } from 'react-router';\n2: import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next';\n3: import { useAuth } from '~/hooks/useAuth';\n4: \n5: export default function Header() {\n6:   const { t, i18n } = useTranslation();\n7:   const { isAuthenticated, user } = useAuth();\n8: \n9:   const toggleLanguage = () => {\n10:     const next = i18n.language === 'en' ? 'ko' : 'en';\n11:     i18n.changeLanguage(next);\n12:   };\n13: \n14:   return (\n15:     <header className=\"border-b\">\n16:       <div className=\"container flex h-16 items-center justify-between mx-auto px-4\">\n17:         <Link to=\"/\" className=\"text-xl font-bold bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-500 to-violet-500 bg-clip-text text-transparent\">\n18:           NestFind\n19:         </Link>\n20:         <nav className=\"flex items-center gap-4\">\n21:           {isAuthenticated ? (\n22:             <>\n23:               <Link to=\"/search\" className=\"text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground\">\n24:                 {t('nav.search')}\n25:               </Link>\n26:               <Link to=\"/favorites\" className=\"text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground\">\n27:                 {t('nav.favorites')}\n28:               </Link>\n29:               <Link to=\"/inquiries\" className=\"text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground\">\n30:                 {t('nav.inquiries')}\n31:               </Link>\n32:               <Link to=\"/profile\" className=\"text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground\">\n33:                 {t('nav.profile')}\n34:               </Link>\n35:               {user?.role === 'admin' && (\n36:                 <Link to=\"/admin\" className=\"text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground\">\n37:                   {t('nav.admin')}\n38:                 </Link>\n39:               )}\n40:             </>\n41:           ) : (\n42:             <>\n43:               <Link to=\"/login\" className=\"text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground\">\n44:                 {t('nav.login')}\n45:               </Link>\n46:               <Link to=\"/signup\" className=\"text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground\">\n47:                 {t('nav.signup')}\n48:               </Link>\n49:             </>\n50:           )}\n51:           <button\n52:             onClick={toggleLanguage}\n53:             className=\"text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded border border-border text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground hover:bg-accent transition-colors\"\n54:             aria-label={t('common.language')}\n55:           >\n56:             {i18n.language === 'en' ? 'KO' : 'EN'}\n57:           </button>\n58:         </nav>\n59:       </div>\n60:     </header>\n61:   );\n62: }\n\n(End of file - total 62 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"import { Link } from 'react-router';\nimport { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next';\nimport { useAuth } from '~/hooks/useAuth';\n\nexport default function Header() {\n  const { t, i18n } = useTranslation();\n  const { isAuthenticated, user } = useAuth();\n\n  const toggleLanguage = () => {\n    const next = i18n.language === 'en' ? 'ko' : 'en';\n    i18n.changeLanguage(next);\n  };\n\n  return (\n    <header className=\"border-b\">\n      <div className=\"container flex h-16 items-center justify-between mx-auto px-4\">\n        <Link to=\"/\" className=\"text-xl font-bold bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-500 to-violet-500 bg-clip-text text-transparent\">\n          NestFind\n        </Link>\n        <nav className=\"flex items-center gap-4\">","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"frontend/app/components/layout/header.tsx","time":{"start":1779192454490,"end":1779192454775}},"id":"prt_e402257df001GI4tJs6KIHVxul","sessionID":"ses_1bfdf015dffez1iatzFjbXquMi","messageID":"msg_e402162e7001vF0HFFZJYFc70T"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779192456584,"sessionID":"ses_1bfdf015dffez1iatzFjbXquMi","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_ia8Bmmh8r8E23TEq53CN9693","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/styling-guide.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/styling-guide.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Styling Guide\n2: \n3: Modern styling patterns using Tailwind CSS 4, Shadcn/UI, and CSS variables.\n4: \n5: ---\n6: \n7: ## Core Concepts\n8: \n9: ### Tailwind CSS 4\n10: \n11: The project uses Tailwind CSS 4 with utility-first styling:\n12: \n13: ```typescript\n14: // Direct utility classes\n15: <div className=\"p-4 mb-3 flex flex-col gap-2\">\n16:   Content\n17: </div>\n18: ```\n19: \n20: ### cn() Utility\n21: \n22: Use `cn()` for conditional class merging (combines `clsx` + `tailwind-merge`):\n23: \n24: ```typescript\n25: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n26: \n27: <div className={cn(\n28:   'p-4 bg-background',\n29:   isActive && 'bg-primary text-primary-foreground',\n30:   isDisabled && 'opacity-50 pointer-events-none'\n31: )} />\n32: ```\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ## CSS Variables (Theme)\n37: \n38: ### Available Color Variables\n39: \n40: Colors are defined in `~/styles/app.css` using oklch color space:\n41: \n42: ```css\n43: :root {\n44:   --background: oklch(1 0 0);\n45:   --foreground: oklch(0.145 0 0);\n46:   --primary: oklch(0.205 0 0);\n47:   --primary-foreground: oklch(0.985 0 0);\n48:   --secondary: oklch(0.97 0 0);\n49:   --secondary-foreground: oklch(0.205 0 0);\n50:   --muted: oklch(0.97 0 0);\n51:   --muted-foreground: oklch(0.556 0 0);\n52:   --accent: oklch(0.97 0 0);\n53:   --accent-foreground: oklch(0.205 0 0);\n54:   --destructive: oklch(0.577 0.245 27.325);\n55:   --border: oklch(0.922 0 0);\n56:   --input: oklch(0.922 0 0);\n57:   --ring: oklch(0.708 0 0);\n58:   /* Chart colors, sidebar colors, etc. */\n59: }\n60: ```\n61: \n62: ### Using Color Variables\n63: \n64: ```typescript\n65: // Via Tailwind classes (preferred)\n66: <div className=\"bg-background text-foreground\" />\n67: <div className=\"bg-primary text-primary-foreground\" />\n68: <div className=\"text-muted-foreground\" />\n69: <div className=\"border-border\" />\n70: <div className=\"bg-destructive\" />\n71: \n72: // Semantic usage\n73: <p className=\"text-muted-foreground\">Secondary text</p>\n74: <button className=\"bg-primary text-primary-foreground\">Button</button>\n75: <div className=\"border border-input\">Input border</div>\n76: ```\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## Dark Mode\n81: \n82: ### How Dark Mode Works\n83: \n84: Dark mode is activated by adding `.dark` class to the document:\n85: \n86: ```css\n87: .dark {\n88:   --background: oklch(0.145 0 0);\n89:   --foreground: oklch(0.985 0 0);\n90:   --primary: oklch(0.922 0 0);\n91:   --primary-foreground: oklch(0.205 0 0);\n92:   /* ... other overrides */\n93: }\n94: ```\n95: \n96: ### Dark Mode Variants\n97: \n98: ```typescript\n99: // Automatic with semantic colors (preferred)\n100: <div className=\"bg-background text-foreground\" />\n101: // Light: white bg, dark text\n102: // Dark: dark bg, light text\n103: \n104: // Explicit dark mode variants\n105: <div className=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\" />\n106: <div className=\"text-gray-900 dark:text-white\" />\n107: ```\n108: \n109: ---\n110: \n111: ## Common Utility Classes\n112: \n113: ### Spacing\n114: \n115: ```typescript\n116: // Padding\n117: <div className=\"p-4\" />      // All sides: 1rem (16px)\n118: <div className=\"px-4\" />     // Horizontal: 1rem\n119: <div className=\"py-4\" />     // Vertical: 1rem\n120: <div className=\"pt-4\" />     // Top only: 1rem\n121: <div className=\"p-2\" />      // All sides: 0.5rem (8px)\n122: \n123: // Margin\n124: <div className=\"m-4\" />      // All sides\n125: <div className=\"mx-auto\" />  // Center horizontally\n126: <div className=\"mt-4 mb-2\" />\n127: \n128: // Gap (for flex/grid)\n129: <div className=\"gap-4\" />    // 1rem gap\n130: <div className=\"gap-2\" />    // 0.5rem gap\n131: ```\n132: \n133: ### Flexbox\n134: \n135: ```typescript\n136: // Basic flex\n137: <div className=\"flex\" />\n138: <div className=\"flex flex-col\" />\n139: <div className=\"flex flex-row\" />\n140: \n141: // Alignment\n142: <div className=\"flex items-center\" />\n143: <div className=\"flex justify-center\" />\n144: <div className=\"flex justify-between\" />\n145: <div className=\"flex items-center justify-center\" />\n146: \n147: // Gap\n148: <div className=\"flex gap-4\" />\n149: <div className=\"flex flex-col gap-2\" />\n150: \n151: // Common pattern\n152: <div className=\"flex items-center justify-between gap-4\">\n153:   <span>Left</span>\n154:   <span>Right</span>\n155: </div>\n156: ```\n157: \n158: ### Grid\n159: \n160: ```typescript\n161: // Basic grid\n162: <div className=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-4\" />\n163: <div className=\"grid grid-cols-3 gap-4\" />\n164: \n165: // Responsive columns\n166: <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4\" />\n167: \n168: // Auto-fit columns\n169: <div className=\"grid grid-cols-[repeat(auto-fit,minmax(200px,1fr))] gap-4\" />\n170: ```\n171: \n172: ### Typography\n173: \n174: ```typescript\n175: // Font size\n176: <p className=\"text-sm\" />    // 14px\n177: <p className=\"text-base\" />  // 16px\n178: <p className=\"text-lg\" />    // 18px\n179: <p className=\"text-xl\" />    // 20px\n180: <p className=\"text-2xl\" />   // 24px\n181: <p className=\"text-3xl\" />   // 30px\n182: \n183: // Font weight\n184: <p className=\"font-normal\" />\n185: <p className=\"font-medium\" />\n186: <p className=\"font-semibold\" />\n187: <p className=\"font-bold\" />\n188: \n189: // Text color\n190: <p className=\"text-foreground\" />\n191: <p className=\"text-muted-foreground\" />\n192: <p className=\"text-primary\" />\n193: <p className=\"text-destructive\" />\n194: ```\n195: \n196: ### Sizing\n197: \n198: ```typescript\n199: // Width\n200: <div className=\"w-full\" />     // 100%\n201: <div className=\"w-1/2\" />      // 50%\n202: <div className=\"w-auto\" />\n203: <div className=\"max-w-md\" />   // max-width: 28rem\n204: <div className=\"max-w-lg\" />   // max-width: 32rem\n205: <div className=\"max-w-xl\" />   // max-width: 36rem\n206: \n207: // Height\n208: <div className=\"h-full\" />\n209: <div className=\"h-screen\" />   // 100vh\n210: <div className=\"min-h-screen\" />\n211: \n212: // Square\n213: <div className=\"size-4\" />     // 1rem x 1rem\n214: <div className=\"size-8\" />     // 2rem x 2rem\n215: ```\n216: \n217: ### Borders & Rounded\n218: \n219: ```typescript\n220: // Border\n221: <div className=\"border\" />\n222: <div className=\"border-2\" />\n223: <div className=\"border border-input\" />\n224: <div className=\"border-b\" />  // Bottom only\n225: \n226: // Rounded corners\n227: <div className=\"rounded\" />\n228: <div className=\"rounded-md\" />\n229: <div className=\"rounded-lg\" />\n230: <div className=\"rounded-full\" />\n231: ```\n232: \n233: ---\n234: \n235: ## Responsive Design\n236: \n237: ### Breakpoints\n238: \n239: ```typescript\n240: // Tailwind default breakpoints\n241: sm: 640px\n242: md: 768px\n243: lg: 1024px\n244: xl: 1280px\n245: 2xl: 1536px\n246: ```\n247: \n248: ### Mobile-First Approach\n249: \n250: ```typescript\n251: // Start with mobile, add breakpoints for larger\n252: <div className=\"\n253:   flex flex-col          // Mobile: column layout\n254:   md:flex-row            // Tablet+: row layout\n255:   gap-4\n256: \">\n257:   <div className=\"\n258:     w-full               // Mobile: full width\n259:     md:w-1/2             // Tablet+: half width\n260:   \">\n261:     Column 1\n262:   </div>\n263:   <div className=\"w-full md:w-1/2\">\n264:     Column 2\n265:   </div>\n266: </div>\n267: ```\n268: \n269: ### Common Responsive Patterns\n270: \n271: ```typescript\n272: // Responsive padding\n273: <div className=\"p-4 md:p-6 lg:p-8\" />\n274: \n275: // Responsive text\n276: <h1 className=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl lg:text-4xl\" />\n277: \n278: // Hide/show on screen sizes\n279: <div className=\"hidden md:block\" />  // Hidden on mobile, visible on tablet+\n280: <div className=\"md:hidden\" />        // Visible on mobile only\n281: \n282: // Responsive grid\n283: <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4\" />\n284: ```\n285: \n286: ---\n287: \n288: ## Common Component Styling\n289: \n290: ### Card Pattern\n291: \n292: ```typescript\n293: <div className=\"rounded-lg border bg-card p-6 shadow-sm\">\n294:   <h3 className=\"text-lg font-semibold\">Title</h3>\n295:   <p className=\"text-muted-foreground\">Description</p>\n296: </div>\n297: ```\n298: \n299: ### Form Input Pattern\n300: \n301: ```typescript\n302: <div className=\"space-y-2\">\n303:   <label className=\"text-sm font-medium\">Label</label>\n304:   <input className=\"\n305:     flex h-9 w-full rounded-md border border-input bg-background\n306:     px-3 py-1 text-sm shadow-sm transition-colors\n307:     placeholder:text-muted-foreground\n308:     focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring\n309:   \" />\n310: </div>\n311: ```\n312: \n313: ### Button Pattern\n314: \n315: ```typescript\n316: // Primary button\n317: <button className=\"\n318:   inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md\n319:   bg-primary text-primary-foreground\n320:   h-9 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium\n321:   hover:bg-primary/90\n322:   transition-colors\n323: \">\n324:   Button\n325: </button>\n326: \n327: // Outline button\n328: <button className=\"\n329:   border border-input bg-background\n330:   hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground\n331: \">\n332:   Outline\n333: </button>\n334: ```\n335: \n336: ### Page Layout Pattern\n337: \n338: ```typescript\n339: <div className=\"min-h-screen bg-background\">\n340:   <header className=\"border-b\">\n341:     <div className=\"container mx-auto px-4 py-4\">\n342:       Header\n343:     </div>\n344:   </header>\n345: \n346:   <main className=\"container mx-auto px-4 py-8\">\n347:     <h1 className=\"text-3xl font-bold mb-6\">Page Title</h1>\n348:     Content\n349:   </main>\n350: </div>\n351: ```\n352: \n353: ---\n354: \n355: ## Shadcn/UI Component Styling\n356: \n357: ### Customizing Shadcn Components\n358: \n359: ```typescript\n360: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n361: import { Card } from '~/components/ui/card';\n362: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n363: \n364: // Add custom classes\n365: <Button className=\"w-full\">Full Width Button</Button>\n366: \n367: // Conditional classes\n368: <Button className={cn(\n369:   'w-full',\n370:   isLoading && 'opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed'\n371: )}>\n372:   Submit\n373: </Button>\n374: \n375: // Override padding\n376: <Card className=\"p-8\">More padding</Card>\n377: ```\n378: \n379: ### CVA Variants\n380: \n381: Shadcn/UI components use CVA (Class Variance Authority) for variants:\n382: \n383: ```typescript\n384: // Button variants\n385: <Button variant=\"default\">Primary</Button>\n386: <Button variant=\"secondary\">Secondary</Button>\n387: <Button variant=\"destructive\">Danger</Button>\n388: <Button variant=\"outline\">Outlined</Button>\n389: <Button variant=\"ghost\">Ghost</Button>\n390: <Button variant=\"link\">Link</Button>\n391: \n392: // Sizes\n393: <Button size=\"sm\">Small</Button>\n394: <Button size=\"default\">Default</Button>\n395: <Button size=\"lg\">Large</Button>\n396: <Button size=\"icon\"><Icon /></Button>\n397: \n398: // Input variants\n399: <Input variant=\"default\" />       // Standard border + indigo focus\n400: <Input variant=\"error\" />         // Red border + red focus ring\n401: \n402: // Select variants\n403: <Select variant=\"default\" />      // Standard filter select\n404: <Select variant=\"compact\" />      // Pagination row selector\n405: <Select variant=\"ghost\" />        // Transparent status dropdown\n406: ```\n407: \n408: ### Variant-First Styling Rule (MANDATORY)\n409: \n410: **This rule applies to ALL reusable components — not just UI primitives.**\n411: \n412: When any reusable component needs visually distinct styles across different call sites, the difference **MUST** be expressed as a cva variant on the component — never as duplicated `className` strings at call sites.\n413: \n414: **Rules:**\n415: 1. Every reusable component **MUST** accept a `className` prop for one-off layout overrides\n416: 2. When the same styling pattern appears at 2+ call sites, it **MUST** be extracted as a cva variant\n417: 3. Semantic states (error, success, warning, loading) **MUST** always be variants, even if used at only 1 call site\n418: 4. `className` is reserved for **one-off, context-specific overrides** (width, height, spacing, positioning)\n419: \n420: | Pattern | Approach | Example |\n421: |---------|----------|---------|\n422: | Error/invalid state | **Variant** | `<Input variant=\"error\" />` |\n423: | Compact/dense layout | **Variant** | `<Select variant=\"compact\" />` |\n424: | Ghost/transparent style | **Variant** | `<Select variant=\"ghost\" />` |\n425: | Any repeated style group | **Variant** | Extract to cva if used 2+ times |\n426: | Icon offset padding | className | `className=\"pl-10\"` |\n427: | Full-width override | className | `className=\"w-full\"` |\n428: | Context-specific height | className | `className=\"h-24\"` |\n429: | Dynamic status color | className | `className={style.text}` |\n430: \n431: **Anti-patterns to reject:**\n432: - Duplicated Tailwind class groups at multiple call sites — extract a cva variant\n433: - Raw `<select>` / `<input>` / `<textarea>` / `<button>` with inline Tailwind — use the UI primitive with variant + className\n434: - Reusable component without `className` prop — every reusable component must accept className\n435: - Creating a new component for a different style of an existing component — add a variant instead\n436: \n437: ---\n438: \n439: ## What NOT to Do\n440: \n441: ### Avoid Inline Style Objects\n442: \n443: ```typescript\n444: // ❌ AVOID - Inline style objects\n445: <div style={{ padding: '16px', marginBottom: '12px' }}>\n446:   Content\n447: </div>\n448: \n449: // ✅ PREFERRED - Tailwind classes\n450: <div className=\"p-4 mb-3\">\n451:   Content\n452: </div>\n453: ```\n454: \n455: ### Avoid CSS-in-JS Libraries\n456: \n457: ```typescript\n458: // ❌ AVOID - styled-components, emotion, etc.\n459: import styled from 'styled-components';\n460: \n461: const StyledDiv = styled.div`\n462:   padding: 16px;\n463: `;\n464: \n465: // ✅ PREFERRED - Tailwind utility classes\n466: <div className=\"p-4\">Content</div>\n467: ```\n468: \n469: ### Avoid Global CSS (except for themes)\n470: \n471: ```typescript\n472: // ❌ AVOID - Custom CSS classes in separate files\n473: // styles.css\n474: .my-custom-button { padding: 16px; }\n475: \n476: // ✅ PREFERRED - Tailwind classes or CVA variants\n477: <Button className=\"px-4\">Button</Button>\n478: ```\n479: \n480: ---\n481: \n482: ## Summary\n483: \n484: **Styling Checklist:**\n485: \n486: - ✅ Use Tailwind CSS utility classes directly\n487: - ✅ Use `cn()` for conditional class merging\n488: - ✅ Use semantic color variables (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`)\n489: - ✅ Mobile-first responsive design\n490: - ✅ Shadcn/UI component variants via CVA\n491: - ✅ Dark mode via CSS variables (automatic)\n492: - ❌ No inline style objects\n493: - ❌ No CSS-in-JS libraries\n494: - ❌ No custom CSS files (except themes)\n495: \n496: **See Also:**\n497: \n498: - [component-patterns.md](component-patterns.md) - Component structure\n499: - [complete-examples.md](complete-examples.md) - Full styling examples\n\n(End of file - total 499 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Styling Guide\n\nModern styling patterns using Tailwind CSS 4, Shadcn/UI, and CSS variables.\n\n---\n\n## Core Concepts\n\n### Tailwind CSS 4\n\nThe project uses Tailwind CSS 4 with utility-first styling:\n\n```typescript\n// Direct utility classes\n<div className=\"p-4 mb-3 flex flex-col gap-2\">\n  Content\n</div>\n```\n\n### cn() Utility","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/docs/styling-guide.md","time":{"start":1779192456295,"end":1779192456583}},"id":"prt_e40225ee6001cpgzzwUkMLU3qb","sessionID":"ses_1bfdf015dffez1iatzFjbXquMi","messageID":"msg_e402162e7001vF0HFFZJYFc70T"}}
